-- Olympus Capital Names Ex-Nomura Banker Katayama as Japan Managing Director
-- Takahiko Hyuga
-- 2010-06-16T10:10:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/olympus-capital-names-ex-nomura-banker-katayama-as-japan-managing-director.html

          
          
             Olympus Capital Holdings Asia , the
Hong Kong private-equity firm with $1.2 billion under management,
hired  Shunji Katayama , a former investment banker at Nomura
Holdings Inc., as a managing director.  
 Katayama, 48, will join Olympus Capitalâ€™s Tokyo office on
June 21, the company said in an e-mailed statement today.  
 Katayama was managing director at  Nomura  before he quit
earlier this year. He had been co-head of investment banking
coverage at Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. after spending eight
years as a senior banker in the general industry group at
 Goldman Sachs Group Inc. , the statement said.  
 The banker has advised Japanese companies in the chemicals,
healthcare, pharmaceutical, consumer, retail and entertainment
industries, according to the statement.  
 The private equity firm aims to have Katayama expand its
franchise in Japan and the rest of Asia,  David Shen , regional
managing director of Olympus Capital, said in the statement.  
